# ResumeAtlas project memory

At the **start of every session**, read **all** files in `/ai-context` before editing product copy, SEO, billing, analytics, or architecture:

1. `ai-context/product-rules.md` — product truth, analysis + optimization benefits, free/paid boundaries
2. `ai-context/product_summary.md` — user-facing benefits, analysis + optimization metrics (reference doc)
3. `ai-context/pricing.md` — Razorpay, starter pack, download gate
4. `ai-context/architecture.md` — system design, funnels, components
5. `ai-context/seo-structure.md` — 68 URLs, clusters, authority pages
6. `ai-context/analytics.md` — GA4 funnel events

## Positioning (non-negotiable)

ResumeAtlas sells **both** apply-readiness **analysis** and **job-specific optimization** — never position as analysis-only.

- **Analysis:** verdict + shortlist odds, role fit for this posting, elimination risks, skill proof map, keyword coverage, selectable recommended fixes
- **Optimization:** JD summary, listed-only → proven, user-selected rejection fixes, impact quantification, editable preview, PDF/DOCX
- **Free tier:** 1 scan / 30 days (no signup) · optimize free after sign-in · **pay only to download**
- **Billing UI:** only `starter` pack ($2.99 / ₹249, 5 credits) is enabled

Canonical benefit copy lives in `app/lib/productBenefits.ts`.
